[4] Vaccination
Date: Thu 4 Mar 2020 14:14 GMT
Source: Guinee News [in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://www.guineenews.org/ebola-seule-la-vaccination-peut-briser-la-chaine-de-transmission-prefet-de-nzerekore/amp/?__twitter_impression=true


As announced in one of our previous editions of the morning, the 2nd shipment of vaccines, which should allow the chain of transmission of the Ebola virus to be broken as quickly as possible in N'Zerekore, has just been received by the local administrative and health authorities.

This 2nd batch of vaccines was conveyed by Dr. Sakoba Keita, the Director General of the National Agency for Health Security (ANSS), who was accompanied by representatives of the WHO.

By receiving these vaccines, the prefect of N'Zerekore expressed to the press not only his joy, but also appealed to the populations to avoid any reluctance to this vaccination campaign: "I am happy to receive these vaccines at the moment. Because only vaccination can allow us to end very quickly with this Ebola virus. It is for this reason that I am asking the population to take more responsibility and to cooperate fully in order to break all forms of reluctance."

For the moment, Guinee News could not know the exact quantity of vaccines received this Thursday [4 Mar 2021].

[Byline: Alpha Oumar Balde]

